---
rule_type: auto
description: "Enforce Python coding standards for Code Index MCP project"
globs: ["**/*.py"]
---

Target Python 3.10+ for all code implementations.
Follow `.pylintrc` configuration: 4-space indentation, 100-character line limit.
Limit function signatures to 7 or fewer parameters.
Use `snake_case` for modules and functions.
Use `PascalCase` for class names.
Use `UPPER_CASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES` for constants.
Prefer explicit imports from sibling packages (`from .services import ...`).
Keep all logging output to stderr as implemented in `server.py`.
Avoid checking in generated `__pycache__` artifacts.
Place source code in `src/code_index_mcp/` with proper module organization.
Use `indexing/` for builders, `services/` for MCP tool implementations, `search/` for query utilities, `utils/` for cross-cutting helpers.
